.TH CORTEX-RULES 1 "2026-03-27" "cortex-rules 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cortex-rules \- Command-line tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cortex-rules
[
B-h
    R | 
        B--help
               R]
.br
.B cortex-rules

ICOMMAND
        R [
           ISUBCOMMAND
                      R] [
                          IARGS
                               R...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cortex-rules
.SH COMMANDS
Available commands:
.TP
.B list
List available rules
.TP
.B status
Show active rule modules
.TP
.B activate
Activate one or more rule modules
.TP
.B deactivate
Deactivate one or more rule modules
.TP
.B edit
Open rule file(s) in $EDITOR
.TP
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT
Override for context directory (set automatically by Claude Code when running plugin commands)
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.claude/
Default context directory containing agents, modes, rules, and other configuration
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cortex-rules-tui (1),
.BR cortex-rules-workflow (1)
